item.title: 814. Binary Tree Pruning
item.description: We are given the head node root of a binary tree, where additionally every node’s value is either a 0 or a 1. Return the same tree where every subtree (of the given tree) not containing a 1 has been removed. (Recall that the subtree of a node X is X, plus every node that is a descendant of X.) item.title: 113. Path Sum II
item.description:
Given a binary tree and a sum, find all root-to-leaf paths where each path’s sum equals the given sum.

Note: A leaf is a node with no children.
